# Project-wide registry namespace for `docker push` / `docker pull`.
#
# Used by ops/release.sh, ops/db/push_image.sh, and the
# dev / prod target host run.sh + push_image.sh — anywhere the docker
# images need to be published or pulled.
#
# Resolution chain (highest priority first):
#   1. Shell env: `export DOCKER_REGISTRY=docker.io/youruser`
#   2. This file (REGISTRY) — first non-empty, non-comment DOCKER_REGISTRY= line
#   3. Auto-detect (lib.sh → detect_default_registry) — docker.io/$USER or empty
#
# Format: a namespace prefix prepended to `image:tag` for push/pull.
#   docker.io/zhangyu528
#   ghcr.io/myorg
#   registry.gitlab.com/mygroup
#
# This file is COMMITTED to git. It is shared project config, not a
# personal secret. Personal secrets (postgres password, AI keys, TTS
# keys) live in `cms/.env` (gitignored) on the CMS host.
#
# Leave this file empty (no uncommented DOCKER_REGISTRY= line) to fall
# back to detect_default_registry() (docker.io/$USER on most dev hosts).
# Uncomment + edit the line below to pin a shared registry for the team.

# DOCKER_REGISTRY=docker.io/youruser
